Thank you so much for the thoughtful response. It immediately made my
morning ten times better.

   I am still living in Sacramento, my family and I go to Temple all the
time so that would be perfect. I have a completely open schedule, any day
and time will work.

   My phone number is +1-916-837-4947. We can schedule something over text.


   Being a music teacher sounds like a lot of fun; I'll definitely have a
lot of questions about that. I started trying to pick guitar back up
because I wanted to play my favorite Radiohead songs, and to be able to
have a means to play melodies that I randomly come up with throughout the
day; it's made me realize how insanely technically  complex music
composition is. I'm hoping that learning from other musicians on physical
instruments will translate over into working on a digital audio workshop.

   I think the last time that we spoke, it was around the time that you got
accepted to the Art Institute (at least I think it was SAIC). That's
awesome that you stuck with it and got your degree, I'm curious to hear how
it compared to school in SF.

   Genuinely, thank you for the words of encouragement. I don't hear people
tell me that I'll be able to pick myself up very often. I'm not proud of
who I've met myself become, so it means a lot to me right now to read that.

Good to hear from you again, let's hang out soon.

